Review: “Would you like a girl’s toy (Poor Things) or a boy’s toy (Beau is Afraid)?”
The way Anna Kendrick says “The original rump shakers!” Movie star! Hail Queen Poppy!!
Damn this Jeffrey Schwartz guy has a stacked résumé
The wa wa waaaa at the end was not cool
These dudes should’ve been in Babylon

As of late I’ve encountered a lot of hand-wringing about films’ raison d'etre. I won’t pile on to that conversation, but I will say how refreshing a movie like Showing Up feels right now. It’s firmly contained in its own world, one that Kelly Reichardt ensures is given a pulse of its own. It has a sense of humor that doesn’t sell out its other ingredients. And in many ways it’s about the reasons for creating something; those that are deeply personal; inconsequential to most, but central to a few
Got me rethinking my next 0 fade

I like how Payne and co use the broader strokes of Hollywood studio filmmaking to expand on the base premise ten times, make plays for excellent character actors and dream up a whole ass world. I wish more grown-up movies had this much imagination
